author: Neil Batey
title: Emmerdale spoilers: Rebecca fears she has killed sister Chrissie in horror fall
text:
Chrissie motionless on the floor after horror fall (Photo: ITV) Share Get soaps   Could   
Who needs enemies when your sister will go to any lengths to destroy you? 
Rebecca plans to surprise her Emmerdale sibling Chrissie by getting her mum’s engagement ring engraved – but is horrified to find she’s lost it. 
In the ITV soap this week, Chrissie seems furious, as is Lawrence when he learns Rebecca got Robert involved. But as the week goes on it becomes clear that evil Chrissie is hiding something: the ring. 
Realising she’s been set up, Rebecca makes a grab for the jewellery. As the girls wrestle, Chrissie topples over the bannister and crashes on to a glass table below. Out of jail... into danger Joanie is finally free after a spell behind bars (Photo: Andrew Boyce) 
Joanie’s spent a month behind bars for punching a policeman (not the smartest move). Now she’s finally let out of jail. 
Joanie (above) leaves prison and is collected by Lisa, who takes her back to Emmerdale. On their drive to the village, the newly-released pensioner is shocked when Lisa tells her she is now back with Joanie’s estranged husband Zak. Joanie is collected from prison by love rival Lisa (Photo: AMY BRAMMALL) Read More 
After a heart-to-heart, Lisa (above) starts to question whether that’s really what she wants – but something awful happens before they get home in the award-winning Yorkshire-set show. Plan turns to ashes Moira and Ross scheme together to nick a motor (Photo: ITV) 
Still grieving for her daughter and reeling from her split with cheating Cain, Moira Barton is a women on the edge. 
And she is furious when she finds out Ross has been keeping a stolen car in one of her barns. 
Later, when her meeting with client Patrick doesn’t go to plan, she gets a chance to wreak revenge. After she finds his car keys on the floor she jumps in the motor and speeds off to Butlers Farm. 
She encourages Ross to flog the vehicle and split the profit – but then finds out there’s an urn of ashes in the boot. It’s a race against time as Moira rushes back to the farm to try to get the human remains before Ross sells the vehicle – and Patrick calls the cops.
